## What this is

An alpha-reader project that runs the v0.4 methodology against a complete (or partial) novel using one or more of the 9 anti-sycophancy-retrofitted v0.4 personas.

Default workflow: single-persona Pass A (clean read). Optional: add Pass B (V2 vs V1 comparison read) if a prior-draft + prior alpha-reader response are available.

## Anti-sycophancy stack (active)

10 universal v0.4 bindings (rating discipline, no hedging, DNF honesty, no conversion arcs, no closing-summary warmth, forced negative generation Q0, mandatory 1-star Q9, comp-anchor strict ranking, Goodreads distribution prediction, authority-relationship inversion).

If Pass B fires: 11th binding adds (no improvement-narrative arcs).

Reflexive Opus 4.7 self-critique pass on every persona response identifies sycophancy artifacts and emits calibrated rating + keep-reading estimates (appended to response file as supplementary signal).

## Pipeline architecture

```
{slug}/
├── CLAUDE.md                          # hard-isolation declaration + provenance
├── book_config.yaml                   # load-bearing — orchestrator reads from this
├── .env                               # Anthropic API key (gitignored)
├── manuscript/
│   └── {manuscript_filename}          # main manuscript (chapter markers normalized)
├── references/
│   ├── personas-snapshot-v0.4.md      # 9-persona reference (toolkit-canonical copy)
│   └── readability-snapshot.md        # textstat metrics panel + persona-prompt block
├── orchestrator/
│   ├── run-alpha-reader.py            # toolkit-canonical orchestrator
│   ├── readability_analyzer.py        # toolkit-canonical analyzer
│   └── auth_probe.py                  # toolkit-canonical auth probe
├── kickoffs/
│   └── {created_date}-alpha-reader.md # this file
└── runs/                              # populated on first fire
    ├── alpha-reader-pass-a-clean/     # Pass A output
    └── alpha-reader-pass-b-comparison/ # Pass B output (if Pass B fires)
```

## How to fire

**Default (single-persona Pass A):**

```bash
cd <project-dir>
python orchestrator/auth_probe.py
python orchestrator/run-alpha-reader.py --pass a --persona {default_persona} --dry-run
# review prompt sample, then fire:
python orchestrator/run-alpha-reader.py --pass a --persona {default_persona}
```

Expected duration: ~3-6 minutes per persona (Sonnet stream + Opus reflexive)
Expected cost: ~$1.20-1.70 per persona (Sonnet) + $0.30 reflexive Opus

**Multi-persona fire** (any subset of marisol-the-whale, tessa-booktok, nadia-dark-fantasy, aaliyah-romantasy, brittany-erotica, kayla-hockey, sienna-fae-court, veronica-the-hatchet, emma-the-surgeon):

```bash
for p in kayla-hockey brittany-erotica veronica-the-hatchet; do
  python orchestrator/run-alpha-reader.py --pass a --persona $p
done
```

## Pre-fire checklist

- [ ] Manuscript path verified: `manuscript/{manuscript_filename}` (chapter markers normalized)
- [ ] book_config.yaml verified (book.title, book.pen_name, book.genre_hint, book.is_complete, cost_cap_usd)
- [ ] Personas snapshot verified: `references/personas-snapshot-v0.4.md` (9 personas)
- [ ] Readability snapshot generated: `references/readability-snapshot.md`
- [ ] .env contains your real direct Anthropic API key
- [ ] auth_probe passes
- [ ] Cost cap acknowledged: ${cost_cap}/pass binding
- [ ] Persona selection decided

## Post-fire deliverables

For each pass, each persona:
- `runs/alpha-reader-pass-{{a,b}}/responses/<persona-id>-response.md` — persona's structured rubric response + reflexive Opus self-critique appended
- `runs/.../_run-report.md` — telemetry, cost, status
- `runs/.../_state.yaml` — atomic state for resume
- `runs/.../_status.json` — JSON-serialized state

